<paragraph blockId="12.[128,768,1735,2087]" lastBlockId="12.[843,1482,151,1021]" pageId="12" pageNumber="21">
D i s c u s s i o n. This generic name was first used by 
<bibRefCitation author="Schlotheim, E. F. von" box="[167,373,1768,1792]" pageId="12" pageNumber="21" refId="ref20364" refString="Schlotheim, E. F. von (1820): Die Petrefactenkunde auf ihrem jetzigen Standpunkte durch die Beschreibung seiner Sammlung versteinerter und fossiler Uberreste des Thier- und Pflanzenreichs der Vorwelt erlautert. - Becker, Gotha, 437 pp." type="book" year="1820">Schlotheim (1820)</bibRefCitation>
for fossils he interpreted as being of grass-like leaves but this is invalid as it pre-dated the starting point for taxonomic nomenclature of fossil plants (ICN, Art. 13.1) as well as lacking a generic diagnosis (ICN, Art. 39.1). However, a review of 
<bibRefCitation author="Schlotheim, E. F. von" box="[549,767,1898,1922]" pageId="12" pageNumber="21" refId="ref20364" refString="Schlotheim, E. F. von (1820): Die Petrefactenkunde auf ihrem jetzigen Standpunkte durch die Beschreibung seiner Sammlung versteinerter und fossiler Uberreste des Thier- und Pflanzenreichs der Vorwelt erlautert. - Becker, Gotha, 437 pp." type="book" year="1820">Schlotheim’s (1820)</bibRefCitation>
work by 
<bibRefCitation author="Ballenstedt, J. - G. - J." box="[229,430,1931,1955]" pageId="12" pageNumber="21" pagination="158 - 176" refId="ref14819" refString="Ballenstedt, J. - G. - J. (1821): Die Petrefactenkunde auf ihrem jetzigem Standpunkte durch die Beschreibung seiner Sammlung versteinerter und fossiler Uberreste des Thier- und Pflanzenreichs der Vorwelt erlautert von E. F. Baron von Schlotheim, Herz. Sachs. Goth. Geh. R. und Kammer-Pras., d. K. Baiersch. Ak. d. Wiss. zu Munchen u. s. w. Mitgliede. Mit 15 Kupfertafeln (in einem abgefonderten Hefte in gr. 4.) Gotha 1820. 432 S. in 8. - Archiv fur die neuesten Entdeckungen aus der Urwelt, 3: 158 - 176." type="journal article" year="1821">Ballenstedt (1821)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned one of the species, “ 
<taxonomicName authority="&quot; SCHLOTHEIM" authorityName="SCHLOTHEIM" box="[140,501,1963,1987]" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Lycopodiopsida (awaiting allocation)" genus="Poacites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lycopodiopsida (awaiting allocation)" pageId="12" pageNumber="21" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="zeaeformis">
<emphasis box="[140,356,1963,1987]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="21">Poacites zeaeformis</emphasis>
” SCHLOTHEIM
</taxonomicName>
, accompanied by a brief description: “auf Tafel XXVI [of 
<bibRefCitation author="Schlotheim, E. F. von" box="[510,699,1995,2020]" pageId="12" pageNumber="21" refId="ref20364" refString="Schlotheim, E. F. von (1820): Die Petrefactenkunde auf ihrem jetzigen Standpunkte durch die Beschreibung seiner Sammlung versteinerter und fossiler Uberreste des Thier- und Pflanzenreichs der Vorwelt erlautert. - Becker, Gotha, 437 pp." type="book" year="1820">Schlotheim 1820</bibRefCitation>
] zwei Abbildungen von 
<taxonomicName box="[326,543,2028,2052]" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Lycopodiopsida (awaiting allocation)" genus="Poacites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lycopodiopsida (awaiting allocation)" pageId="12" pageNumber="21" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="zeaeformis">
<emphasis box="[326,543,2028,2052]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="21">Poacites zeaeformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, welche Grasart mit dem Mais sehr viel Ähnlichkeit hat, verzüglich auf den selteren Exemplaren die noch Stengelblaettern zeigen.” Since this review only mentioned this one species under the generic name 
<taxonomicName box="[997,1089,217,240]" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Lycopodiopsida (awaiting allocation)" genus="Poacites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lycopodiopsida (awaiting allocation)" pageId="12" pageNumber="21" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[997,1089,217,240]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="21">Poacites</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, this species diagnosis may also be used for the genus (ICN, Art. 38.5), thereby validating the publication of the generic name in this review. Nevertheless, the name is in practice unusable as the 
<typeStatus box="[1241,1335,315,339]" pageId="12" pageNumber="21">syntypes</typeStatus>
(as illustrated in 
<bibRefCitation author="Schlotheim, E. F. von" box="[872,1061,347,371]" pageId="12" pageNumber="21" refId="ref20364" refString="Schlotheim, E. F. von (1820): Die Petrefactenkunde auf ihrem jetzigen Standpunkte durch die Beschreibung seiner Sammlung versteinerter und fossiler Uberreste des Thier- und Pflanzenreichs der Vorwelt erlautert. - Becker, Gotha, 437 pp." type="book" year="1820">Schlotheim 1820</bibRefCitation>
: pl. 26, figs 1, 2) show different types of fossils and the diagnosis is effectively meaningless in identifying a species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[843,1482,151,1021]" pageId="12" pageNumber="21">
Apparently unaware of Ballenstedt’s (1822) review, 
<bibRefCitation author="Brongniart, A." box="[843,1057,477,501]" pageId="12" pageNumber="21" pagination="203 - 240" refId="ref15150" refString="Brongniart, A. (1822 a): Sur la classification et la distribution des vegetaux fossiles en general, et sur ceux des terrains de sediment superieur en particulier. Introduction, Chapitre I. - Memoires du Museum d'Histoire Naturelle, 8: 203 - 240, pls 1 - 4." type="journal article" year="1822">Brongniart (1822a)</bibRefCitation>
later illegitimately used the generic name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Paterson" authorityYear="1844" box="[914,1027,509,533]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Calamitaceae" genus="Pothocites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Equisetales" pageId="12" pageNumber="21" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[914,1027,509,533]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="21">Pothocites</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for a rather different, grass-like fossil, which he named 
<taxonomicName authority="BRONGNIART. This" authorityName="BRONGNIART. This" box="[1020,1418,542,566]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Calamitaceae" genus="Pothocites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Equisetales" pageId="12" pageNumber="21" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="carinata">
<emphasis box="[1020,1228,542,566]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="21">Pothocites carinata</emphasis>
BRONGNIART. This
</taxonomicName>
looks remarkably like a Carboniferous arborescent lycopsid leaf that today is usually named 
<taxonomicName authority="LINDLEY et HUTTON, 1832" authorityName="LINDLEY et HUTTON" authorityYear="1832" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Sigillariaceae" genus="Cyperites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lepidodendrales" pageId="12" pageNumber="21" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bicarinata">
<emphasis box="[1161,1385,607,631]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="21">Cyperites bicarinata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Lindley, J. &amp; Hutton, W." pageId="12" pageNumber="21" pagination="49 - 166" refId="ref19230" refString="Lindley, J., Hutton, W. (1832): The fossil flora of Great Britain. Volume 1 (2). - W. J. Ridgeway and Sons, London, pp. 49 - 166." type="book chapter" year="1832">LINDLEY et HUTTON, 1832</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(e.g. compare with 
<bibRefCitation author="Rex, G." box="[1251,1360,640,664]" pageId="12" pageNumber="21" pagination="65 - 85" refId="ref20098" refString="Rex, G. (1983): The compression state of preservation of Carboniferous lepidodendrid leaves. - Review of Palaeobotany and Palynology, 39: 65 - 85. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / 0034 - 6667 (83) 90011 - 8" type="journal article" year="1983">Rex 1983</bibRefCitation>
). Although 
<bibRefCitation author="Brongniart, A." box="[843,1049,672,696]" pageId="12" pageNumber="21" pagination="203 - 240" refId="ref15150" refString="Brongniart, A. (1822 a): Sur la classification et la distribution des vegetaux fossiles en general, et sur ceux des terrains de sediment superieur en particulier. Introduction, Chapitre I. - Memoires du Museum d'Histoire Naturelle, 8: 203 - 240, pls 1 - 4." type="journal article" year="1822">Brongniart (1822a)</bibRefCitation>
does not refer to any of the four species described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Schlotheim, E. F. von" box="[982,1183,704,729]" pageId="12" pageNumber="21" refId="ref20364" refString="Schlotheim, E. F. von (1820): Die Petrefactenkunde auf ihrem jetzigen Standpunkte durch die Beschreibung seiner Sammlung versteinerter und fossiler Uberreste des Thier- und Pflanzenreichs der Vorwelt erlautert. - Becker, Gotha, 437 pp." type="book" year="1820">Schlotheim (1820)</bibRefCitation>
, he unequivocally attributed the generic name 
<taxonomicName box="[1038,1130,738,761]" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Lycopodiopsida (awaiting allocation)" genus="Poacites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lycopodiopsida (awaiting allocation)" pageId="12" pageNumber="21" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1038,1130,738,761]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="21">Poacites</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as he used it to Schlotheim and provided generic a diagnosis very similar to that of 
<taxonomicName authority="SCHLOTHEIM ex BALLENSTEDT. However" authorityName="BALLENSTEDT. However" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Lycopodiopsida (awaiting allocation)" genus="Poacites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lycopodiopsida (awaiting allocation)" pageId="12" pageNumber="21" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1390,1482,770,793]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="21">Poacites</emphasis>
SCHLOTHEIM ex BALLENSTEDT. However
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[1316,1444,803,826]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Calamitaceae" genus="Pothocites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Equisetales" pageId="12" pageNumber="21" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="carinata">
<emphasis box="[1316,1444,803,826]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="21">P. carinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is quite different from Schlotheim’s 
<typeStatus box="[1218,1274,835,859]" pageId="12" pageNumber="21">types</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[1317,1409,835,858]" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Lycopodiopsida (awaiting allocation)" genus="Poacites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lycopodiopsida (awaiting allocation)" pageId="12" pageNumber="21" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1317,1409,835,858]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="21">Poacites</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and it would be difficult to see how both could be meaningfully included within the same fossil-genus. 
<taxonomicName authority="SCHLOTHEIM ex BRONGNIART" authorityName="BRONGNIART" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Lycopodiopsida (awaiting allocation)" genus="Poacites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lycopodiopsida (awaiting allocation)" pageId="12" pageNumber="21" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1258,1350,900,923]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="21">Poacites</emphasis>
SCHLOTHEIM ex BRONGNIART
</taxonomicName>
should therefore be regarded as a later homonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="SCHLOTHEIM ex BALLENSTEDT" authorityName="BALLENSTEDT" box="[1004,1428,965,989]" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Lycopodiopsida (awaiting allocation)" genus="Poacites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lycopodiopsida (awaiting allocation)" pageId="12" pageNumber="21" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1004,1096,965,988]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="21">Poacites</emphasis>
SCHLOTHEIM ex BALLENSTEDT
</taxonomicName>
and therefore regarded as illegitimate.
</paragraph>
